<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-818-028  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 818 028.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>The Seybold Report on Publishing Systems  Oct 23 1989 v19 n4p26(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Seybold Publications Inc. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Verity finds the Topic. (Topic document management system)(product announcement)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   Verity Inc. (product introduction).andO;Product:   Topic (Data base management system) (product introduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionDocument Management SystemsInformation Storage and RetrievalLibrary Networks.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Verify finds the Topic Verity had its document management system on display.andO;In essence, the product is a fast and flexible document retrieval or librarysystem.andM;Topic can work in both an ad hoc and more systematic fashion.andP;  For ad hocqueries, the user simply creates a profile of the type of document he islooking for and begins a search.andP;  For more repetivie use of a database,&quot;libraries&quot; of retrieval topics can be carefully established in advance, theapplied to a database search.andP;  These are analogous to formats of proprietarySQL-like queries against subject matter.andP;  Librarians or experts can buildthese retrieval in advance for novice users who can use them as is, modifythem, or combine them for more specific searches.andM;The difference between this type of product and may other library andretrieval systems is the way in which the system queries the databse.andP;  Inmost other systems we have used, the search is based on words or combinationsof words, using Boolean expressions to tie these words or phrases together.andO;In Verity's system, the selection criteria are based on a higher level ofsearch: the &quot;topic&quot; level.andP;  Topics are defined as tree structures that relatewords together to form a hierarchy, which defines selection topics such as&quot;foreign debt stories.&quot;andM;Topic works in conjunction with standard database structures such as thoserunning under Oracle, Sybase and Ingres.andP;  The product works in severaldifferent environments, including VMS, MS-DOS, and Unix.andP;  It was runningunder Sun View at the show.andM;For those who have the time to set up these topic queries, the system will bevery effective.andP;  For others (such as magazine and newspaper writers) who needquick access on more of an ad hoc basis, we think that more conventionalsystems will be appropriate.andO;</TEXT></DOC>